Colouration. Head uniformly orange. Pronotal disc orange with white scales along apical margin. Male tegmen yellow; in dorsal view, apex with broad black margin; black band not continuing to lateral field (
Fig. 4
). Femur pale orange. Abdomen with tergite (including abdominal apex) black, covered by yellow brown scales; sternite white except the apical sternites. Male paraproct process white. Cercus light brown.
